^-{    The Stayman Convention    }
|FP||AT|
The Stayman Convention is used to find a 4-4 major suit fit in NT auctions.|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


AT|
You should only use Stayman if you have a |FP|2|CP|8|at|medium (8-9)|FP||CP||AT| or |FP|2|CP|8|at|maximum (10 or more)|FP||CP||AT| hand.
Do not bid Stayman if you have a |CP|8|AT|minimum (0 to 7 points)|CP||AT| hand. 
(The Garbage Stayman Convention is described in the Advanced Topics at the end of this tutorial. 
If you decide to play garbage Stayman, then you can bid Stayman when you are 4-4 in the majors with a minimum response.)|
